Adds Dynamic DNS (DDNS) support for the Kea DHCP server.

Manages the kea-dhcp-ddns daemon configuration including TSIG keys,
forward and reverse DNS zones, and per-subnet DDNS policy settings
for both DHCPv4 and DHCPv6.

Integrates with the core Kea DHCP plugin via the plugins_run() hook
mechanism to inject DDNS parameters into kea-dhcp4.conf and kea-dhcp6.conf.

Plugin Changelog
================

1.3.3_1

* Remove pkg update from post-install hook to avoid fingerprint errors

1.3.3

Changed:
* Moved to banzai-plugins repository
* Updated package URL to banzai-plugins documentation

1.3.2

Added:
* Core patch for OPNsense 26.7 (alpha)
* generate-patch.sh script for automated core patch creation
* RELEASING.md and PATCHING.md documentation

Changed:
* Regenerate 26.7.patch against 26.7.a tag

1.3.1

Changed:
* Rewrite build.sh for remote build with upgrade/fresh-install testing

1.3

Added:
* GitHub Pages pkg repo for UI plugin details
* Register/deregister plugin with firmware on install/remove
* Build script improvements (auto-update GitHub Pages repo)

1.2

Added:
* Per-subnet ddns-replace-client-name option for both DHCPv4 and DHCPv6
* Documentation with Sphinx HTML and Markdown generation
* Updated README for DHCPv6 support and pkg install instructions
* Pre-install hook to reverse core patch before upgrade

1.1

Added:
* DHCPv6 DDNS support â€” per-subnet6 DDNS policy and overlay injection into kea-dhcp6.conf
* Subnet6 DDNS tab in the UI for managing DHCPv6 DDNS assignments
* Core patch now also hooks KeaDhcpv6.php (kea_dhcpv6_config)

1.0

Added:
* TSIG key management (HMAC-MD5 through HMAC-SHA512)
* Forward and reverse DNS zone configuration
* Per-subnet DDNS policy (send updates, qualifying suffix, conflict resolution)
* Automatic overlay injection into kea-dhcp4.conf via plugins_run() hooks
* kea-dhcp-ddns daemon configuration generation
* Log file viewer for kea-dhcp-ddns

WWW: https://brendanbank.github.io/banzai-plugins/releases/26.1/kea_ddns.html
